author: Gamers Nexus
description:
In dedication to Gordon Mah Ung. Sponsor: Hyte Y70 Touch Infinite on their site https://geni.us/Ir9vKEK
Wendell and I have talked about Gordon a lot over this year, and in honor of him as a mutual friend, we decided to bring back the topic that kicked it all off: Is Intel Actually Screwed? Last time Wendell joined, we talked about Linux benchmarking (linked below) and whether or not x86 was screwed, but now, it's time to get back to what the hell is going on at Intel.

Watch our Linux benchmarking prep video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5O6tQYJSEMw
Watch our x86 vs ARM video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zxP6B2HZ_IY
And go check out Wendell! https://www.youtube.com/c/Level1Techs
Check out the series that kicked it all off with our friend Gordon: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-wGd6Dsm_lo

title: Round 5: "Is Intel Actually Screwed?" ft. Wendell of Level1 Techs
